ORBITRON-ME: Orbitron-Multiplet-Edac Suite
===========================================

This software integrates multiple computational engines with modern GUI interfaces.

COMPONENT ATTRIBUTIONS:
-----------------------

1. GUI Interface & Linux Compatibility Implementation
   Copyright (c) 2024 TeslaYet
   Licensed under MIT License (see below)

2. EDAC Computational Engine (Edac 2/ directory)
   Original work by F. Javier Garcia de Abajo
   Copyright (c) 1997-2000 F. Javier Garcia de Abajo
   
3. Multiplet Theory Computational Engine, Cluster Generation Tools, and Visualization Tools
   Original work by Professor Peter Krüger, University of Chiba
   This includes:
   - Multiplet theory calculations (Multiplet2/RPES/src/ directory)
   - Cluster structure generation tools (cluster2edac.c, edacclusterfile/ directory)
   - Visualization and analysis tools (intens_stereo_*.c, rpededac.c, etc.)

ACADEMIC USE:
-------------
If you use this software in academic research, please cite:

- For the integrated suite: TeslaYet (2024). ORBITRON-ME. https://github.com/TeslaYet/ORBITRON-ME
- For EDAC calculations: The relevant publications by F. Javier Garcia de Abajo
- For Multiplet theory and associated tools: The relevant publications by Professor Peter Krüger

